  <h2>What is a Computer?</h2>
  <p>
    A <strong>computer</strong> is an electronic machine that can receive information (called <em>input</em>), process it, store it, and show results (called <em>output</em>). Computers are everywhere — in your phone, your school, even in your microwave!
  </p>

  <h2>The Two Main Parts</h2>
  <p>Every computer has two key things:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hardware</strong> — The physical parts you can touch, like the screen, keyboard, and mouse.</li>
    <li><strong>Software</strong> — The programs and apps that run on the computer, like games, browsers, and word processors.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Main Parts of a Computer</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🖥️ <strong>Monitor</strong> — The screen that displays everything you see.</li>
    <li>⌨️ <strong>Keyboard</strong> — Used to type letters, numbers, and commands.</li>
    <li>🖱️ <strong>Mouse</strong> — Lets you point and click on things on the screen.</li>
    <li>🧠 <strong>CPU</strong> — The "brain" that processes everything.</li>
    <li>💾 <strong>Storage</strong> — Where files, photos, and programs are saved.</li>
    <li>🔌 <strong>Power Supply</strong> — Gives electricity to all the parts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>A Simple Analogy</h2>
  <blockquote>
    Think of a computer like a chef in a kitchen. The <strong>keyboard and mouse</strong> are the ingredients going in, the <strong>CPU</strong> is the chef doing the cooking, and the <strong>monitor</strong> is the plate where the finished dish is served!
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Types of Computers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🖥️ <strong>Desktop Computer</strong> — Sits on a desk, most powerful for its size.</li>
    <li>💻 <strong>Laptop</strong> — A portable computer you can take anywhere.</li>
    <li>📱 <strong>Smartphone</strong> — A tiny computer that fits in your pocket!</li>
    <li>⌚ <strong>Smartwatch</strong> — An even tinier computer worn on your wrist.</li>
  </ul>

